<% provide(:title, "Boost your vocabulary in a fun and simple way.") %>
<% provide(:header, "Boost your vocabulary in a fun and simple way.") %>

<%= render "shared/flash_messages" %>

<div class="top-section">
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-sm-6 col-sm-offset-3 center">
			<h1>Leksi</h1>
			<h3>
				Boost your vocabulary in a fun and simple way.
			</h3>
		</div>
	</div>

	<br>

	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-xs-6 col-xs-offset-3 col-sm-2 col-sm-offset-5 center
								data-url btn-custom-get-started"
				 data-url="/get_started">
			Get started
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="thin-gray-section center">
	<h3>
		Design based on research studies into how vocabulary is learned best*
	</h3>

	<div class="guest-homepage-images-container col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="research-first-image"></div>

				<h4>Personalization</h4>

				<p>
					Collect, organize, and use words that you want
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="research-second-image"></div>

				<h4>Learning in chunks</h4>

				<p>
					Focus on a limited number of words at a time
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="research-third-image"></div>

				<h4>A holistic approach</h4>

				<p>
					Learn different parts of the word
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="research-fourth-image"></div>

				<h4>Multiple exposures</h4>

				<p>
					Be exposed to words in various contexts
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="research-fifth-image"></div>

				<h4>Re-play</h4>

				<p>
					Engage in activities that reuse a lot of words at one time
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="research-sixth-image"></div>

				<h4>...and more word-learning strategies!</h4>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="clear"></div>

	<br>

	<small class="gray">
		*(Anderson, 1999; Beck, McKeown, &amp; Kucan, 2002; Nation,
		2001; Stahl, 2005; Stahl &amp; Nagy, 2006)
	</small>
</div>


<div class="fat-section center">
	<h3>
		Leksi makes the learning experience fun and engaging.
	</h3>

	<div class="guest-homepage-images-container col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="gamification-first-image"></div>

				<h4>Game on!</h4>

				<p>
					Master each word in your list by completing our games
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="gamification-second-image"></div>
				<h4>Checkpoints</h4>

				<p>
					Instantly see your progress as you learn
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>

		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="gamification-third-image"></div>

				<h4>Level Up</h4>

				<p>
					Earn experience points, level up, and achieve your weekly goals
					with each game you complete
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="col-sm-6">
				<div class="gamification-fourth-image"></div>
				<h4>Leaderboard</h4>

				<p>
					Climb the Leaderboard ranks - and stay there!
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="clear"></div>
</div>

<div class="thin-gray-section">
	<div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">
		<div class="center">
			<%= image_tag("multiple_devices_color_100.png") %>
			<h4>Use Leksi on any software or device</h4>
		</div>

		<p>
			Be more productive wherever you are, on the go. To use Leksi, all you need
			is internet access and a web browser (e.g. Safari, Chrome, Firefox).
			This means you can use Leksi on any phone, tablet, laptop, or computer
			device.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div class="clear"></div>
</div>

<div class="thin-white-section">
	<div class="col-sm-8 col-sm-offset-2">
		<div class="center">
			<%= image_tag("school_color_100.png") %>
			<h4>Leksi for Schools</h4>
		</div>

		Vocabulary is the biggest indicator of a student's success. See why
		it's crucial to not only literacy development, but also other academic
		areas as well.

		<p>
			<%= mail_to "help@leksi.education", "Bring Leksi to your classroom",
				  subject: "Bring Leksi to My Classroom"
			%>
		</p>
	</div>
</div>
